Figures

get_pred_mu_ci <- 
  function(dist_boot, dat){
    avg_all <- 
      colMeans(dist_boot$t)
    quantile_all <-
      apply(dist_boot$t, 2, 
            function(x) quantile(x, c(0.025,.975)))
    
    avg_all <- 
      aggregate(avg_all, list(dat$gop_binary, dat$time_day), mean)
    
    avg_quant <- 
      apply(quantile_all, 1, 
            function(x) aggregate(x, list(dat$gop_binary, dat$time_day), mean))
    
    avgs_dem <- 
      avg_all[avg_all$Group.1==0,]$x
    avgs_rep <- 
      avg_all[avg_all$Group.1==1,]$x
    
    q25_dem <- 
      avg_quant$`2.5%`[avg_quant$`2.5%`$Group.1==0,]$x
    q97_dem <- 
      avg_quant$`97.5%`[avg_quant$`97.5%`$Group.1==0,]$x
    
    q25_rep <- 
      avg_quant$`2.5%`[avg_quant$`2.5%`$Group.1==1,]$x
    q97_rep <- 
      avg_quant$`97.5%`[avg_quant$`97.5%`$Group.1==1,]$x
    
    out <- 
      data.frame(cbind(avgs_dem, 
                     q25_dem,
                     q97_dem,
                     avgs_rep,
                     q25_rep,
                     q97_rep))
    
    return(out)    
  }


get_pred_mu_ci_state <- 
  function(dist_boot, dat, state){
    all_sims <- dist_boot$t
    all_sims <- 
      all_sims[, dat$state_name == state]
    avg_all <- 
      colMeans(all_sims)
    quantile_all <-
      apply(all_sims, 2, 
            function(x) quantile(x, c(0.025,.975)))
    dat <-
      subset(dat, state_name == state)
    avg_all <- 
      aggregate(avg_all, list(dat$gop_binary, dat$time_day), mean)
    
    avg_quant <- 
      apply(quantile_all, 1, 
            function(x) aggregate(x, list(dat$gop_binary, dat$time_day), mean))
    
    avgs_dem <- 
      avg_all[avg_all$Group.1==0,]$x
    avgs_rep <- 
      avg_all[avg_all$Group.1==1,]$x
    
    q25_dem <- 
      avg_quant$`2.5%`[avg_quant$`2.5%`$Group.1==0,]$x
    q97_dem <- 
      avg_quant$`97.5%`[avg_quant$`97.5%`$Group.1==0,]$x
    
    q25_rep <- 
      avg_quant$`2.5%`[avg_quant$`2.5%`$Group.1==1,]$x
    q97_rep <- 
      avg_quant$`97.5%`[avg_quant$`97.5%`$Group.1==1,]$x
    
    out <- 
      data.frame(cbind(avgs_dem, 
                     q25_dem,
                     q97_dem,
                     avgs_rep,
                     q25_rep,
                     q97_rep))
    
    return(out)    
  }

plot_preds_quick <- 
  function(plotdat,
           lwd = 1){
    if ("avgs_dem" %in% names(plotdat)){
       polygon(
      x = c(seq(0,81),rev(seq(0,81))),
      y = c(plotdat$q97_dem*100,
           rev(plotdat$q25_dem*100 )),
      col = rgb(0.4,.4,.8,.5),
      border = F
      )
  
    lines(x = seq(0,81),
        y = plotdat$avgs_dem*100,
        lwd = lwd, col = rgb(0,0,182 ,maxColorValue = 255))
  
    }
    
    if ("avgs_rep" %in% names(plotdat)){
        polygon(
          x = c(seq(0,81),rev(seq(0,81))),
          y = c( plotdat$q97_rep*100,
                 rev(plotdat$q25_rep*100 )),
          col = rgb(0.8,.4,.4,.5),
          border = F
        )
        
        lines(x = seq(0,81),
            y = plotdat$avgs_rep*100,
            lwd = lwd, col = rgb(153,0,0 ,maxColorValue = 255))
    }
   

  }

plot_data_with_sims <- function(fit_dat,
                                plotdat,
                                y_var = "",
                                y_label ="",
                                main_label = ""){
  
  plot(NA,
       xlim = c(0,81),
       ylim = c(-50, 100),
       xlab = "", ylab = "",
       axes = F)
  
  grid()
  
  date_labs <- unique(fit_dat$date)[axTicks(1)+1]
  
  axis(1, lwd = 1.2, cex.axis = .8, 
       labels = rep("", length(axTicks(1))), at = axTicks(1))
  
  text(axTicks(1), par("usr")[3]-10.55, 
     srt = 45, adj = 1, xpd = TRUE,
     labels = date_labs, cex = 0.7)
  
  axis(2, lwd = 1.2, las =2, cex.axis = .7,
       at = seq(-50,100,25),
       labels = paste(seq(-50,100,25), "%") )
  mtext(y_label, 2, 3, font = 1,cex = 0.8)
  mtext(main_label, 3, 0, font = 1, cex = 0.6)
  
  yy <- fit_dat[, y_var]*100
  with(
    fit_dat,
    {
      points(y = yy,
         x = jitter(as.numeric(time_day)),
         pch = 19,
         cex = 0.1,
         col = ifelse(gop_binary==0,
                 my_blue_lght,
                 my_pink_lght))
      day_avg <- 
        by(yy[fit_dat$gop_binary==0], time_day[fit_dat$gop_binary==0], mean)
      lines(day_avg, lwd = 1, lty = 2, col = rgb(0,0,182 ,maxColorValue = 255))
            day_avg <- 
        by(yy[fit_dat$gop_binary==1], time_day[fit_dat$gop_binary==1], mean)
      lines(day_avg, lwd = 1, lty = 2, col = rgb(153,0,0 ,maxColorValue = 255))
    }
  
  )
  
  plot_preds_quick(plotdat, lwd = 2)
}

  predict(fit_visit_time_part_sat_noint)

county_avg_predV <- 
  aggregate(cbind(plotdatV*100, fit_dat_V$gop_binary, fit_dat_V$county_population),
            list(fit_dat_V$county_fips), mean)
names(county_avg_predV) <- c("county_fips", "y_pred", "gop_binary", "county_population")

counties_sf <- 
  get_urbn_map("counties", sf = F)

counties_sf$county_fips <-
  as.numeric(counties_sf$county_fips)


all_predV <- 
  left_join(counties_sf,
            county_avg_predV,
          by = c("county_fips"))

all_predV_gop <-
  all_predV%>%
  filter(gop_binary == 1)

all_predV_dem <-
  all_predV %>%
  filter(gop_binary == 0)

long_lat <- 
  with(counties_sf, 
       aggregate(cbind(long, lat), list(county_fips), mean))
names(long_lat)[1] <- "county_fips"

long_lat <-
  left_join(long_lat, county_avg_predV, "county_fips")
long_lat_gop <-
  subset(long_lat, gop_binary==1)
long_lat_dem <-
  subset(long_lat, gop_binary==0)



alpha_val <- 185

#pdf("figure_USA_visiting_pop.pdf", width = 8, height = 6)
ggplot() +
  geom_polygon(data = urbnmapr::states, 
               mapping = aes(long, lat, group = group),
             fill = "#aaaaaa", color = "#ffffff", size = 0.1) + 
  coord_map(projection = "albers", lat0 = 39, lat1 = 45) +
  geom_point(data = long_lat_gop, 
             mapping = aes(x=long, y = lat, 
                           size = (county_population),
                           color = y_pred)) +
    labs(color = "% Reduction") +
  scale_color_gradient(low = rgb(255, 245, 240, max = 255, alpha = alpha_val), 
                       high = rgb(103, 0, 15, max = 255, alpha = alpha_val),
                      limits = c(-80, 80)) +
    guides(size = FALSE) +
    new_scale_color() +
    labs(color = "% Reduction") +
  geom_point(data = long_lat_dem, 
             mapping = aes(x=long, y = lat, 
                           size = (county_population),
                           color = y_pred)) +
  scale_color_gradient(low = rgb(247, 251, 255, max = 255, alpha = alpha_val), 
                       high = rgb(8, 48, 107, max = 255, alpha = alpha_val),
                      limits = c(-80, 80)) +

  geom_polygon(data = urbnmapr::states, 
               mapping = aes(long, lat, group = group),
             fill = NA, color = "#000000" , size = 0.5)  +
  labs(color = "% Reduction",
       title = "Predicted % Reduction in Visiting Non-Essential Services \nby County Partisan Lean",
       caption = "Red: Trump lean in 2016 vote\nBlue: Clinton lean in 2016 vote") +
  theme(plot.margin = margin(t = 0, r = 0, b = 0, l = 0),
        axis.line=element_blank(),
        axis.text.x=element_blank(),
        axis.text.y=element_blank(),
        axis.ticks=element_blank(),

timer <- Sys.time()
dist_boot <-
  bootMer(fit_dist_time_foxlean_sat_noint, predict,
          nsim = 1000, use.u = T,
          parallel = "snow", ncpus = 10)
Sys.time()-timer

save(dist_boot,
     file = paste0("model_files/", "LMER_BOOT_FOX_fit_dist_time_part_sat_noint.rda"))
